reviews.review_text: old favorite This has to be my favorite China Cat/Rider. Hi energy great transition. Have had this on XL2 since 81. Its great to get it for download. Would love a SB of this one. Archive rocks!

G.D. at the office I'm thoroughly enjoying this show at the office. The audience gets quite loud at times, but I'm dealing with it.
What ever happened to gdlive.com ? I used to log onto that site quite a bit. It's been down for ages !

Peace,
Bob
New Jersey

Some Moments Here I like the dynamics in Althea, some real quiet moments. Then a very nice MNS to end the first set. Fanning from both Bob and Jer.

Great setlist, but all in all much like alot from this run - not a lot of facemelting performances. Solid nonetheless and if your into this SF>NYC Dead Set/Reckoning run this show is well worth the DL.

It is a fine sounding aud. to boot. RCMH has great acoustics as these posted aud's are proving. Super vocal captures.
You cant go wrong All of these shows from sept-oct 1980 are stellar. Good set lists good music and lots of highlights. Download all of them and see for yourself.
Nice Recording I was at this show, and it was the highlight of my musical life.  It's great to get a copy of the show after all of these years.
magic 30 years ago today i attended this show. it was a magical evening. loved the three sets. i was also present at 10/25 show & 17 at the time.
My fave Radio City show My fave show of the Radio City run. Great show!

Fav RCMH Love this show and haven't listen to in years! Great second set all the way. Candyman smokes and is on Dead Set. 
Fun stuff!

terrible why is this even posted.
one of the shittiest recordings i have ever heard on here.
AWFUL.
THE WHEEL IS TURNING A decent recording. Terrapin was great and I always love those early 80's Space melting into the Wheel. It's like landing in a peaceful meadow. :)
